description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic candidate to join our patient safety team at North West Boroughs Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust as we develop our plans for the implementation of the new national patient safety initiatives across the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Head of Risk and Patient Safety you will manage the broad risk and patient safety agenda. The role requires oversight and management of all serious incidents, patient safety incidents, risk registers, patient safety alerts and supporting the lessons learned agenda. You will lead a dedicated team in including specialised patient safety reviewers and will support borough leadership teams in enabling the delivery of localised improvement as a result of learning from incidents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have line management responsibility for the patient safety team. A key feature of this role is the being a supportive leader for the embedding of the safety culture as part of our Trust Quality Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Nursing and Governance Directorate you will work in collaboration with our Patient Safety Panel, Learning from Deaths, Health and Safety, Complaints and Patient Experience functions to support the organisation in the delivery of our strategic objectives and new ways of working for the delivery of the Patient Safety Incident Response Framework (PSIRF).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
